Soweto business mogul Dr. Richard Maponya has died. He was 99. Maponya passed after a short illness in the early hours of this morning. One of his most recognizable developments was the Maponya Mall. He was also one of the founding members of the National African Federated Chamber of Commerce and Industry Nafcoc. Maponya family spokesperson Mandla Sibeko speaks to us. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Soweto businessman and property mogul Dr Richard Maponya has died at age 99, after a short illness. Maponya family spokesperson Mandla Sibeko said he died in the early hours of the morning. Maponya was the founder and first president of the National African Federated Chamber of Commerce and Industry (Nafcoc).